# Consumer .npmrc for installing @low-orbit-studio/visor-themes-private
#
# Lives at the repo root because npm in workspace mode ignores .npmrc files
# inside individual workspace packages. Vercel's install ran from packages/docs/
# initially refused to read packages/docs/.npmrc with the warning
# "ignoring workspace config at /vercel/path0/packages/docs/.npmrc". The root
# .npmrc is read for all workspace installs.
#
# This file scopes only the @low-orbit-studio package namespace to GitHub
# Packages and provides the auth token via the GITHUB_PACKAGES_TOKEN
# environment variable. The PAT must belong to a user with read access to the
# `low-orbit-studio/visor-themes-private` repo (classic PAT with read:packages,
# or a fine-grained PAT with Contents: read on that repo — but classic PATs are
# more reliably accepted by the GitHub Packages npm registry).
#
# When GITHUB_PACKAGES_TOKEN is unset or invalid, npm install of
# @low-orbit-studio/visor-themes-private will fail authentication. Because the
# package is listed as an optional dependency in packages/docs/package.json,
# npm install continues; the docs build then renders /themes/private as 404.

@low-orbit-studio:registry=https://npm.pkg.github.com
//npm.pkg.github.com/:_authToken=${GITHUB_PACKAGES_TOKEN}
